# Vercel Blob (Cart2Barrel)

Docs: [Vercel Blob](https://vercel.com/docs/vercel-blob), [Blob SDK](https://vercel.com/docs/vercel-blob/using-blob-sdk), [server upload](https://vercel.com/docs/vercel-blob/server-upload).

## Project setup (Vercel dashboard + local)

1. **Connect Blob to the Vercel project** — Storage → Blob → create/connect store. This injects **`BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN`** into the project env. Use a **public** store (this app saves public URLs in Postgres).
2. **Local env** — `vercel link` then `vercel env pull`, or copy a read/write token into **`.env`** only (never commit). Restart `npm run dev` after changing env.
3. **Package** — `@vercel/blob` is already a dependency; do not add a second blob client.
4. **Placeholder** — `.env.example` documents `BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=`; never paste real tokens into rules, commands, or tracked files.

## How this repo uploads (not the Vercel avatar template)

Vercel’s Next.js quickstart uses a **Route Handler** (`/api/.../route.ts`) + client `fetch`. **Do not add that pattern** for new features unless explicitly requested.

Cart2Barrel uploads via **Server Actions** that call `put()` from `@vercel/blob`, then persist `blob.url` with **Drizzle**:

- `src/actions/upload-item-request-product-image.ts` — `product-images/{itemRequestId}/…`
- `src/actions/admin-upload-retailer-receipt-images.ts` — `retailer-receipts/{orderItemId}/…`
- `src/actions/upload-warehouse-barcode-image.ts` — `warehouse-barcodes/{orderItemId}/…`

Use **`getBlobReadWriteToken()`** / **`blobReadWriteNotConfiguredMessage()`** from `src/lib/vercel-blob-env.ts` when the token is missing.

```typescript
const token = getBlobReadWriteToken();
if (!token) return { ok: false, message: blobReadWriteNotConfiguredMessage() };

const blob = await put(pathname, file, {
  access: "public",
  token,
  contentType: file.type || undefined,
});
// then db.update(...).set({ ...Url: blob.url })
```

## Size limits

- **Vercel server upload** (file through your server / Server Action on Vercel): **~4.5 MB** max per request. See [client uploads](https://vercel.com/docs/vercel-blob/client-upload) if you need larger files.
- App validation today allows up to **8 MB** (`RETAILER_RECEIPT_IMAGE_MAX_BYTES` in `src/lib/retailer-receipt-images.ts`) — uploads **> 4.5 MB will fail on Vercel** unless you switch to client uploads or lower the app limit.

## Access mode

- **`access: 'public'`** — anyone with the URL can fetch; do not store secrets in public blobs.
- Private blobs need authorized reads in your app (`get()` + Clerk); see `.cursor/rules/cart2barrel-clerk-authz.mdc`.

## Pathnames

- **Immutable paths** — `{prefix}/{resourceId}/{uuid}.{ext}`; avoid reusing the same pathname (CDN/cache).

| Prefix | Use |
|--------|-----|
| `product-images/{itemRequestId}/…` | Customer product photos |
| `retailer-receipts/{orderItemId}/…` | Admin receipt screenshots |
| `warehouse-barcodes/{orderItemId}/…` | Inbound barcode photos |

## Auth, validation, UI

- **Clerk** — verify owner or admin before `put()` and DB updates (`.cursor/rules/cart2barrel-clerk-authz.mdc`).
- **Zod** — validate ids at the trust boundary; multipart may use `FormData` internally but **do not** type the exported action arg as `FormData` (`.cursor/rules/cart2barrel-rsc-server-actions-zod.mdc`).
- **UI** — shadcn file inputs; use `<img>` or configure `next/image` `remotePatterns` for blob hosts (`.cursor/rules/cart2barrel-shadcn-ui.mdc`).

## Deletes

- Clearing a URL in Postgres **does not** delete the blob; call **`del()`** only when product intent is to remove storage.
